page.title: 05BIRD SURVEY=VICARAGE GARDEN
page.content: Resident and migratory birds visit the bird table. Blackbirds, Song and Mistle Thrushes, Robins, Chaffinches and Greenfinches, while Blue Tits, Coletits and Great tits enjoy the nut feeder. Wrens and Hedge Sparrows slip along in the box hedges. Tree Creepers, Nuthatches hunt the tree bark. Occasionally a Spotted Woodpecker and once a Green Woodpecker visited. Pigeons, Collar Doves and Cock Pheasant with his hens and Red Legged Partridge shelter in the shrubs. At night Little Owls and a Tawny Owl screech and hoot and the Barn Owl floats by. Once we saw a Brambling and a Pied Wagtail. Fieldfares and Redwings squabble over fallen fruit. The Cuckoo visits regularly while a Sparrowhawk once devoured a Chaffinch before our eyes.
